Conover, Respondent, v. Lennon, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County,

General Term.

May 12, 1892.) Action by David Conover against W. F. Lennon.

Argued before Bookstaver and Bisohoff, JJ.

W. H. Gardner, for appellant. James Kearney, for respondent.

*911Ho opinion. Motion for leave to appeal to the court of appeals denied, w ith $10 costs. For decision on appeal, see 19 N. Y. Supp. 910. See, also, 18 N. Y. Supp. 162.
